From: 4noha
Subject: subr_suspend / subr_autoconf: noisy phase + per-device markers (diagnostic only)
License: ISC (this patch modifies OpenBSD source and inherits ISC; see ../LICENSE-ISC)

diag-suspend-verbose.diff
=========================

Diagnostic-only kernel patch for OpenBSD/armv7 (jcs/openbsd-src rk3128)
used to localize the DM250 "intermittent suspend hang" symptom — no
panic, no ddb trace, just a frozen console. The patch instruments two
layers:

  1. kern/subr_suspend.c::sleep_state()
     - "susp: phase QUIESCE  start/end"
     - "susp: phase SUSPEND  start/end"
     - "susp: phase POWERDOWN start/end"
     - "susp: gosleep (CPU halt) ..." / "susp: gosleep returned, ..."
     - "susp: phase RESUME   start/end"
     - "susp: phase WAKEUP   start/end"
     - "susp: suspend_finish"
     Failure paths (EIO / EDEADLK) also emit a "failed" line before the
     goto.

  2. kern/subr_autoconf.c::config_suspend()
     Immediately BEFORE each (*ca->ca_activate)() call, emits:
         "susp: <ACT> <devname>\n"
     switch()-gated to DVACT_QUIESCE / SUSPEND / RESUME / WAKEUP /
     POWERDOWN only, so normal DVACT_DEACTIVATE ticks stay silent.

How to read the output
----------------------

On a successful suspend/resume the console shows the full pipeline:
    susp: phase QUIESCE start
    susp: QUIESCE wsdisplay0
    susp: QUIESCE bwfm0
    ...
    susp: phase QUIESCE end
    susp: phase SUSPEND start
    ...
    susp: gosleep (CPU halt) ...
    susp: gosleep returned, beginning resume
    susp: phase RESUME start
    susp: RESUME ...
    ...
    susp: suspend_finish

On a hang, the LAST line on the framebuffer identifies either
  - the phase the suspend reached (printf is emitted BEFORE
    config_suspend_all is called), or
  - the specific device whose ca_activate is currently spinning or
    deadlocked (printf is emitted BEFORE (*ca->ca_activate)() is
    called).

Take a photo of the screen at hang time — the last "susp:" line names
the suspect.

Limitations / caveats
---------------------

- printf() goes through wsdisplay (framebuffer). Once wsdisplay itself
  is QUIESCE'd, subsequent "susp:" lines may not actually paint. The
  last visible line on the framebuffer should still be either the
  wsdisplay QUIESCE marker or an in-flight device just before it.
- If a hang happens deep in DVACT_SUSPEND where interrupts are already
  off (intr_disable() has run by then) and a driver spin-locks the SoC
  bus, framebuffer DMA may be quiesced and the very last printf can be
  lost in the console buffer that never gets pushed. Treat the last
  visible line as "the suspect or one step before the suspect".
- This patch is intentionally noisy. NOT for production: every
  suspend/resume cycle prints ~50-100 lines to the console. Swap it in
  to chase a hang, take the photo, swap it back out.

Build / deploy
--------------

This diff stacks on top of the rest of the rk3128 patch set
(dwmmc-resume-pwrseq / dwmmc-resume-full-cycle, bcmbt-delay-2s,
bus_space_notimpl-align-clang22, bwfm-sdio-resume-guard,
bwfm-suspend-down v3, ieee80211-media-status-nullguard, ...). Apply
with `patch -p0` from /usr/src and rebuild GENERIC; see
docs/cross-build.md.

After collecting diagnostics, back it out with:
    patch -p0 -R < diag-suspend-verbose.diff

--- sys/kern/subr_suspend.c.orig
+++ sys/kern/subr_suspend.c
@@ -94,10 +94,13 @@
 #endif /* HIBERNATE */

 	sensor_quiesce();
+	printf("susp: phase QUIESCE start\n");
 	if (config_suspend_all(DVACT_QUIESCE)) {
+		printf("susp: phase QUIESCE failed (EIO)\n");
 		error = EIO;
 		goto fail_quiesce;
 	}
+	printf("susp: phase QUIESCE end\n");

 	vfs_stall(curproc, 1);
 #if NSOFTRAID > 0
@@ -135,10 +138,13 @@
 	cold = 2;	/* Force other code to delay() instead of tsleep() */
 	intr_enable_wakeup();

+	printf("susp: phase SUSPEND start\n");
 	if (config_suspend_all(DVACT_SUSPEND) != 0) {
+		printf("susp: phase SUSPEND failed (EDEADLK)\n");
 		error = EDEADLK;
 		goto fail_suspend;
 	}
+	printf("susp: phase SUSPEND end\n");
 	suspend_randomness();
 	if (sleep_setstate(v)) {
 		error = ENOTBLK;
@@ -152,14 +158,18 @@
 		 * when we get to DVACT_POWERDOWN.
 		 */
 		boothowto |= RB_POWERDOWN;
+		printf("susp: phase POWERDOWN start\n");
 		config_suspend_all(DVACT_POWERDOWN);
+		printf("susp: phase POWERDOWN end\n");
 		boothowto &= ~RB_POWERDOWN;

 		if (cpu_setperf != NULL)
 			cpu_setperf(0);
 	}

+	printf("susp: gosleep (CPU halt) ...\n");
 	error = gosleep(v);
+	printf("susp: gosleep returned, beginning resume\n");

 #ifdef HIBERNATE
 	if (sleepmode == SLEEP_HIBERNATE) {
@@ -169,7 +179,9 @@
 #endif /* HIBERNATE */

 fail_pts:
+	printf("susp: phase RESUME start\n");
 	config_suspend_all(DVACT_RESUME);
+	printf("susp: phase RESUME end\n");

 fail_suspend:
 	intr_disable_wakeup();
@@ -198,7 +210,9 @@
 	bufq_restart();

 fail_quiesce:
+	printf("susp: phase WAKEUP start\n");
 	config_suspend_all(DVACT_WAKEUP);
+	printf("susp: phase WAKEUP end\n");
 	sensor_restart();

 #ifdef HIBERNATE
@@ -216,6 +230,7 @@
 	sys_sync(curproc, NULL, NULL);
 	if (cpu_setperf != NULL)
 		cpu_setperf(perflevel);	/* Restore hw.setperf */
+	printf("susp: suspend_finish\n");
 	sleepmode = suspend_finish(v);
 	if (sleepmode != SLEEP_RESUME)
 		goto top;
--- sys/kern/subr_autoconf.c.orig
+++ sys/kern/subr_autoconf.c
@@ -828,7 +828,26 @@
 {
 	const struct cfattach *ca = dev->dv_cfdata->cf_attach;
 	int r;
+	const char *actname;

+	/*
+	 * Diagnostic: print "susp: <ACT> <devname>" immediately BEFORE the
+	 * device's activate hook runs, so a suspend hang inside a driver
+	 * leaves the suspect device name as the last line on the console.
+	 * Gated to suspend/resume-class actions only (no spam from normal
+	 * DEACTIVATE tick paths).
+	 */
+	switch (act) {
+	case DVACT_QUIESCE:	actname = "QUIESCE";	break;
+	case DVACT_SUSPEND:	actname = "SUSPEND";	break;
+	case DVACT_RESUME:	actname = "RESUME";	break;
+	case DVACT_WAKEUP:	actname = "WAKEUP";	break;
+	case DVACT_POWERDOWN:	actname = "POWERDOWN";	break;
+	default:		actname = NULL;		break;
+	}
+	if (actname != NULL)
+		printf("susp: %s %s\n", actname, dev->dv_xname);
+
 	device_ref(dev);
 	if (ca->ca_activate)
 		r = (*ca->ca_activate)(dev, act);
